HEADWORD: Deloul
<hw>De*loul"</hw> <pr>(d⟦asl⟧*l⟦oomac⟧l")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Prob. of Arabic or Bedouin origin.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A special breed of the dromedary used for rapid traveling; the
swift camel; -- called also <altname>herire</altname>, and
<altname>maharik</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Delph</ent>⟦br⟧
